    {
      "id": "fc60db0c4a4f9b898a91e3506844297dea73b832",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-07 18:52:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhy would a race with the list being empty or not cause the wakeup to be missed?\n\nIf it goes from empty to non-empty while being read, The thread will just go back to sleep. But why is that different than the case where the list wasn't empty to begin with?\n\nAnd why doesn't the thread racing with the original wakeup (thread modifying the list), send another wakeup at a later time when the list is empty again?\n\nI guess I just don't understand why the wakeup is missed well enough to understand the fix.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2b4f53434efd8a0c42c14359f15e56bd64f0b175",
      "author": {
